        "description": {
            "value": "<p>The touch of undeath runs through your blood. Your family tree might contain powerful undead, like a vampire.</p>\n<p><strong>Tradition</strong> divine</p>\n<p><strong>Bloodline Skills</strong> Intimidation, Religion</p>\n<p><strong>Sorcerous Gifts</strong> cantrip @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.spells-srd.Item.Void Warp], 1st: @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.spells-srd.Item.Harm], 2nd: @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.spells-srd.Item.See the Unseen], 3rd: @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.spells-srd.Item.Bind Undead], 4th: @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.spells-srd.Item.Talking Corpse], 5th: @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.spells-srd.Item.Invoke Spirits], 6th: @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.spells-srd.Item.Vampiric Exsanguination], 7th: @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.spells-srd.Item.Execute], 8th: @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.spells-srd.Item.Canticle of Everlasting Grief], 9th: @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.spells-srd.Item.Wails of the Damned]</p>\n<p><strong>Bloodline Spells</strong> initial: @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.spells-srd.Item.Undeath's Blessing], advanced: @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.spells-srd.Item.Drain Life], greater: @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.spells-srd.Item.Grasping Grave]</p>\n<p><strong>Blood Magicâ€”Stolen Life</strong> You can channel the necromantic energy in your blood. Either you gain temporary Hit Points equal to the spell's rank that last until the start of your next turn, or a target takes 1 void damage per spell rank (if the spell already deals initial void damage, combine this with the spell's initial damage before determining weaknesses and resistances).</p>"
